From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 21:22:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: stop DAMON contexts when damon_start() fails

For making the error handling simple.

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index fac52ed252743..99eab523d4d11 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -2096,8 +2096,10 @@ int damon_start(struct damon_ctx **ctxs, int nr_ctxs, bool exclusive)
 
 	for (i = 0; i < nr_ctxs; i++) {
 		err = __damon_start(ctxs[i]);
-		if (err)
+		if (err) {
+			damon_stop(ctxs, i);
 			break;
+		}
 		nr_running_ctxs++;
 	}
 	if (exclusive && nr_running_ctxs)
-- 
2.47.3

